54c87752-8d2d-46e5-bc7b-58f414fd127f	00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001	3dad173b-57aa-ef7e-36cd-f5dea33f2225	Identity and Access Management Upgrade	IAM-AMD-001	Design and implement an enterprise-wide Identity and Access Management (IAM) Solution to strengthen authentication, authorization, user lifecycle management, and access governance across the organization’s applications, infrastructure, and digital services. The project will deliver centralized identity administration, role-based access control, privileged access governance, single sign-on, multi-factor authentication, audit logging, and integration with enterprise directories and critical business systems. The objective is to improve security, regulatory compliance, operational efficiency, and controlled access to organizational resources.	The Identity and Access Management (IAM) Solution project aims to establish a secure, centralized, and policy-driven framework for managing digital identities and access rights across the institution. The solution will cover identity provisioning and deprovisioning, authentication services, multi-factor authentication, single sign-on, role-based and policy-based access controls, privileged account management integration, access review workflows, and comprehensive audit trails. The project is intended to reduce unauthorized access risks, enhance compliance with internal security policies and regulatory expectations, and improve visibility, governance, and operational control over user access across enterprise platforms.	Scope\n\nProject Scope\nThe Identity and Access Management (IAM) Solution project covers the design, deployment, integration, and governance of a centralized platform for managing user identities and access rights across the organization’s digital ecosystem. The project will include identity lifecycle management for onboarding, role changes, transfers, suspension, and exit of staff and third parties; centralized authentication and authorization services; Single Sign-On (SSO); Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA); Role-Based Access Control (RBAC); policy-based access controls where applicable; privileged access governance integration; password and credential policy enforcement; self-service password reset; access request and approval workflows; periodic access recertification; audit logging and reporting; and integration with enterprise directories such as Active Directory / LDAP, email platforms, business applications, infrastructure systems, and security monitoring tools.\n\nThe scope also includes security architecture design, implementation standards, configuration of access policies, pilot rollout, phased enterprise deployment, user training, administrator training, documentation, support model definition, and post-implementation stabilization. The project will establish governance processes for access control, segregation of duties, user accountability, and compliance evidence generation.\n\nIn Scope\n\nCentralized identity repository and user account administration\n\nJoiner, mover, leaver lifecycle automation\n\nSingle Sign-On (SSO) for approved enterprise applications\n\nMulti-Factor Authentication (MFA) for critical and privileged access\n\nRole-Based Access Control (RBAC) and access profile definition\n\nAccess request, approval, and provisioning workflows\n\nAccess review and recertification processes\n\nAudit trail, activity logging, and compliance reporting\n\nIntegration with Active Directory, LDAP, HR sources, email, and key enterprise applications\n\nPrivileged account governance integration\n\nPolicy design for authentication, authorization, and password/security controls\n\nUser and administrator training\n\nDeployment, testing, go-live, and hypercare support\n\nOut of Scope\n\nFull replacement of every legacy application where integration APIs do not exist\n\nCustom redevelopment of non-compatible business applications beyond access integration needs\n\nEnterprise network redesign outside IAM security dependencies\n\nNon-identity-related cybersecurity tools unless directly required for IAM integration\n\nMajor HR transformation beyond user identity source alignment	Business Case\n\nBusiness Case\nThe organization currently faces increasing security, operational, and compliance risks arising from fragmented identity stores, inconsistent access provisioning practices, weak authentication controls, excessive manual user administration, and limited visibility into who has access to critical systems. As the organization grows in scale, complexity, and digital dependence, the absence of a centralized Identity and Access Management framework exposes it to unauthorized access, delayed deprovisioning, privilege misuse, audit exceptions, insider threats, operational inefficiencies, and regulatory non-compliance.\n\nThe proposed IAM Solution will provide a unified and policy-driven mechanism for managing digital identities and access privileges across enterprise systems. By centralizing identity governance and strengthening authentication and authorization controls, the project will significantly reduce access-related risks, improve compliance posture, and enhance operational efficiency. Automated provisioning and deprovisioning will reduce delays and human errors in user access administration. Strong authentication, SSO, and MFA will improve both security and user experience. Role-based access models and periodic access reviews will strengthen control over privileged and sensitive systems. Comprehensive logging and reporting will provide management, auditors, and regulators with improved visibility and traceability.\n\nThis project is justified on the basis of its strategic value in improving enterprise security, enforcing accountability, reducing fraud and misuse risks, supporting digital transformation, and ensuring that access to information assets is granted strictly on the basis of business need and approved authority. It will also reduce administrative overhead, standardize access governance processes, improve response time for onboarding and role changes, and create a scalable foundation for future security and compliance initiatives.\n\nExpected Business Benefits\n\nReduced risk of unauthorized access and insider abuse\n\nFaster and more controlled user onboarding, transfer, and exit processing\n\nImproved compliance with internal policies, audit requirements, and regulatory expectations\n\nEnhanced visibility into user access rights across systems\n\nReduced manual effort and operational overhead for IT and security teams\n\nStronger protection of critical systems through MFA and privileged access controls\n\nBetter user experience through Single Sign-On and self-service capabilities\n\nImproved governance, accountability, and audit readiness\n\nStrategic Justification\n\nSupports enterprise cybersecurity strengthening\n\nEnables secure digital transformation and system integration\n\nImproves governance over users, roles, and privileges\n\nProvides a scalable foundation for Zero Trust and access governance maturity\n\nAligns access management with operational, compliance, and risk-management objectives	0f6fe766-af61-4610-b8c4-371b42fe6d5f	f782c2e1-6050-4ce0-a609-224e484328d2	active	green	high	2026-01-01	2026-12-31	2026-03-04	2026-03-31	5000000.00	2000000.00	40.00	\N	2026-03-02 10:20:49.996286+00	2026-03-21 12:18:46.152405+00	db40aa8c-dc75-1e84-8fc9-ef0f59c80a90	{}
